President Joe Biden has declared a state of emergency in the Commonwealth of the Northern Mariana Islands due to the effects of Typhoon Mawar. This declaration allows the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to coordinate disaster relief efforts and provide assistance to the affected areas. FEMA is authorized to mobilize necessary resources and equipment to alleviate the impacts of the emergency. Emergency protective measures will be funded at 75 percent by the federal government. Benigno B. Ruiz of FEMA has been appointed to coordinate recovery operations in the affected areas. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.